["stu","I think volunteering is one of the most effective ways to develop <em>civic</em> awareness in young people.","adj. 作前置定语修饰 awareness",M+" I think + "+OBJ+" volunteering is one of the most effective ways + 不定式(to develop civic awareness in young people)","我认为志愿服务是培养年轻人公民意识最有效的方式之一。"],
["stu","Andrew's point about <em>civic</em> duty resonates with me, but I worry that mandatory programs may backfire.","adj. 作前置定语修饰 duty",M+" Andrew's point about civic duty resonates with me + 转折(but) + "+M+" I worry + "+OBJ+" that mandatory programs may backfire","Andrew关于公民责任的观点引起了我的共鸣，但我担心强制项目可能适得其反。"],
["write","True <em>civic</em> participation goes beyond mere voting — it includes community involvement, informed debate, and collective problem-solving.","adj. 作前置定语修饰 participation",M+" True civic participation goes beyond mere voting — "+M+" it includes community involvement, informed debate, and collective problem-solving","真正的公民参与不仅仅是投票——它包括社区参与、知情辩论和集体解决问题。"],
["write","I believe that <em>civic</em> education should be woven into every subject, not confined to a single required course.","adj. 作前置定语修饰 education",M+" I believe + "+OBJ+" that civic education should be woven into every subject + 比较(not confined to a single required course)","我认为公民教育应该融入每个学科，而不是局限于一门必修课。"],
["write","By requiring volunteer work, schools send a powerful message about the importance of <em>civic</em> engagement in a democratic society.","adj. 作前置定语修饰 engagement",PART+" By requiring volunteer work(方式状语) + "+M+" schools send a powerful message + 介词短语(about the importance of civic engagement in a democratic society)","通过要求志愿服务，学校传递了一个关于公民参与在民主社会中重要性的有力信息。"],
["arg","Nations with strong traditions of <em>civic</em> education tend to have higher voter turnout and lower rates of corruption.","adj. 作前置定语修饰 education",M+" Nations(主语) + 介词短语(with strong traditions of civic education) + tend to have higher voter turnout and lower rates of corruption","拥有深厚公民教育传统的国家往往有更高的投票率和更低的腐败率。"],
["arg","If we truly value <em>civic</em> responsibility, we must create environments where it can flourish naturally, not be imposed by decree.","adj. 作前置定语修饰 responsibility",COND+" If we truly value civic responsibility + "+M+" we must create environments + "+ATTR+" where it can flourish naturally + 比较(not be imposed by decree)","如果我们真正重视公民责任，就必须创造让它自然蓬勃发展的环境，而非通过法令强加。"],
["sum","In conclusion, fostering <em>civic</em> values requires a comprehensive approach that combines education, opportunity, and the freedom to engage on one's own terms.","adj. 作前置定语修饰 values",M+" fostering civic values(动名词作主语) requires a comprehensive approach + "+ATTR+" that combines education, opportunity, and the freedom + 不定式(to engage on one's own terms)","总之，培养公民价值观需要一种综合方法，结合教育、机会和按自己方式参与的自由。"]
